org.mitre.tdp.boogie

Enum LegType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<LegType>
      • org.mitre.tdp.boogie.LegType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<LegType>

    public enum LegType
extends java.lang.Enum<LegType>
    Aka Path Terminator. For graphical pictures of what these represent it is recommended to look at attachment 5 of the Arinc Specification Document. Note each leg type is also a predicate over the Leg data type enforcing the existence of key fields.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • IF

        public static final LegType IF
        Initial Fix. Defines a fix as a point in space.

      • TF

        public static final LegType TF
        Track to a Fix. Defines a great circle track over the ground between two known fixes.

      • CF

        public static final LegType CF
        Course to a Fix. Defines a specified course to a fix.

      • DF

        public static final LegType DF
        Direct to a Fix. Defines an unspecified track starting from an unspecified location to a fix.

      • FA

        public static final LegType FA
        Fix to an Altitude. Defines a specified track over ground from a database fix to a specified altitude at an unspecified position.

      • FC

        public static final LegType FC
        Track from a Fix for a Distance. Defines a specific track over ground from a fix for a specific distance.

      • FD

        public static final LegType FD
        Track from a Fix to a DMS Distance. Defines a specific track over ground from a fix to a specific DME distance (the DME will be referenced and must exist).

      • FM

        public static final LegType FM
        Fix to Manual Termination. Defines a specified track over ground from a fix until manual termination of the leg.

      • CA

        public static final LegType CA
        Course to an Altitude. Defines a course to specific altitude at an unspecified location.

      • CD

        public static final LegType CD
        Course to a DME Distance. Defines a course to a specific DME distance which corresponds to an existing navaid.

      • CI

        public static final LegType CI
        Course to an Intercept. Defines a specified course to a subsequent leg.

      • CR

        public static final LegType CR
        Course to a Radial Termination. Defines a course to a specified radial from a VOR navaid.

      • RF

        public static final LegType RF
        Constant Radius Arc. Defines a constant radius turn between two fixes, lines tangent to the arc and a center fix.

      • AF

        public static final LegType AF
        Arc to Fix. Defines a track over ground at a specified constant distance from a DME navaid.

      • VA

        public static final LegType VA
        Heading to an Altitude Termination. Defines a heading to a specific altitude termination at an unspecified position.

      • VD

        public static final LegType VD
        Heading to a DME Distance Termination. Defines a specified heading to terminating at a specified distance from a DME navaid.

      • VI

        public static final LegType VI
        Heading to an Intercept. Defines a heading to intercept the subsequent leg at an unspecified position.

      • VM

        public static final LegType VM
        Heading to a Manual Termination. Defines a specified heading until a manual termination.

      • VR

        public static final LegType VR
        Heading to a Radial Termination. Defines a heading to specified radial from a VOR navaid.

      • PI

        public static final LegType PI
        Procedure Turn. Defines a course reversal starting at the specified fix. Includes an outbound leg followed by a left or right turn and a 180 degree course reversal to intercept the next leg. Note - A maximum excursion time and distance is included as a data field.

      • HA

        public static final LegType HA
        Holding in Lieu of Procedure Turn. Defines a holding pattern in lieu of a procedure turn course reversal or terminal procedure referenced mandatory holding pattern. Leg time or distance is included. HA = Altitude Termination

      • HF

        public static final LegType HF
        Holding in Lieu of Procedure Turn. Defines a holding pattern in lieu of a procedure turn course reversal or terminal procedure referenced mandatory holding pattern. Leg time or distance is included. HF = Single circuit terminating at a fix

      • HM

        public static final LegType HM
        Holding in Lieu of Procedure Turn. Defines a holding pattern in lieu of a procedure turn course reversal or terminal procedure referenced mandatory holding pattern. Leg time or distance is included. HM = Manual Termination
